From: Warwick Brown <me@moonman.me.uk>
Date: Thu, 2 Jul 2026 14:39:06 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 2/6] =?UTF-8?q?phase=203a:=20toolchest=20libs=20=E2=80=94?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=20Darwin=20alloca.h=20+=20point=20yacc/lex=20at=20Heirloom?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

libcommon/_alloca.h:
    The Apple branch used to include <stdlib.h>, assuming Darwin's
    stdlib.h declared alloca(3) directly. Modern macOS SDKs (Xcode 12+)
    moved the declaration back to the system <alloca.h> gated on
    _DARWIN_C_SOURCE. Use include_next <alloca.h> to reach the SDK
    header past this local shim.

toolchest/build/mk.config:
    YACC and LEX now point at /opt/heirloom/ccs/bin/yacc and .../lex
    installed by Phase 2. Ensures the toolchest's bc/nawk/oawk are
    fed by the same grammar tools they will ship alongside, avoiding
    subtle divergence between system bison and Heirloom yacc.

Libs built: libwchar (widechar shim, largely unused on Darwin),
libcommon (getopt/gmatch/pfmt/regexpr/iblok/oblok), libuxre (POSIX RE),
_install/install_ucb helper. libcommon warnings for strtol.o and
pathconf.o carrying no symbols are expected — those TUs are guarded
out on platforms where libc already provides the interface (Darwin
does), leaving empty .o files.
---
 build/mk.config     |  4 ++--
 libcommon/_alloca.h | 16 ++++++++++++++--
 2 files changed, 16 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/build/mk.config b/build/mk.config
index 85d173e..91f4fdf 100644
--- a/build/mk.config
+++ b/build/mk.config
@@ -234,13 +234,13 @@ LNS = ln -s
 # Yacc implementations known to work with the Heirloom Toolchest are
 # the original Unix yacc, Berkeley yacc, and GNU bison -y (v. 1.875).
 #
-YACC = yacc
+YACC = /opt/heirloom/ccs/bin/yacc
 
 #
 # Lex implementations known to work with the Heirloom Toolchest are
 # most derivatives of the original Unix lex and flex.
 #
-LEX = lex
+LEX = /opt/heirloom/ccs/bin/lex
 
 #
 # Whether to use the supplied widechar emulation library. This should
diff --git a/libcommon/_alloca.h b/libcommon/_alloca.h
index dc2afe5..d034389 100644
--- a/libcommon/_alloca.h
+++ b/libcommon/_alloca.h
@@ -22,6 +22,18 @@
 /*	Sccsid @(#)_alloca.h	1.5 (gritter) 1/22/06	*/
 
 #if defined (__FreeBSD__) || defined (__NetBSD__) || defined (__OpenBSD__) || \
-	defined (__DragonFly__) || defined (__APPLE__)
+	defined (__DragonFly__)
 #include <stdlib.h>
-#endif	/* __FreeBSD__, __NetBSD__, __OpenBSD__, __DragonFly__, __APPLE__ */
+#endif	/* __FreeBSD__, __NetBSD__, __OpenBSD__, __DragonFly__ */
+
+#if defined (__APPLE__)
+/*
+ * Darwin port: shim originally assumed Darwin declared alloca(3) in
+ * <stdlib.h>. Modern macOS SDKs (Xcode 12+) put the declaration back
+ * in the system <alloca.h> under _DARWIN_C_SOURCE, so <stdlib.h> alone
+ * no longer covers it. Delegate to the system <alloca.h> via
+ * include_next; -D_DARWIN_C_SOURCE is set in build/mk.config.
+ * -- Heirloom Darwin port.
+ */
+#include_next <alloca.h>
+#endif	/* __APPLE__ */
